klung im vorchristlichen Imperium Romanum aus verschiedenen Perspektiven wieder auf.  aRecent research on the religious history of the Roman imperial period has clearly shown that the notion of "Roman paganism" having been transformed by "Eastern religions" was a mistaken one. The positive value of this critique is less clear, however. The studies in this volume reexamine the parallels between the evolution of Empire and religion in the pre-Christian Imperium Romanum from various perspectives.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAntike. 4aKaiserzeit. 4aReligionsgeschichte. 4aRom. 7aRELIGION / Antiquities & Archaeology.2bisacsh  aRoman imperial period.  aancient history of religion.1 aArnhold, Marlis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlömer, Michael , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlömer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBremmer, Jan N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEckhardt, Benedikt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEckhardt, Benedikt, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLepke, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrothmann, Meret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWohlthat, Urs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZimmermann, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255